cozy and warm on our next camping trip.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When it comes to covering outdoor gear, I’ve been fairly busy writing a few gear round-ups of my own. My articles over at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.businessinsider.com/\">Business Insider</a>&nbsp;include my selection of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.businessinsider.com/best-backpacking-tent\">best backpacking tents</a>, the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.businessinsider.com/best-backpacking-stoves\">best backpacking stoves</a>, and the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.businessinsider.com/best-bike-rack\">best bike racks for your car</a>. I even put together an extensive list of gear that you’ll want to use for&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.insider.com/backyard-camping\">camping in your own backyard</a>. After all, many of us are ready to get outside and sleep under the stars, we’re just not quite able to go to any campsites just yet.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>During the COIVD-19 outbreak, bikes have suddenly become a hot commodity. So much so that many bike shops are completely sold out of some models and bike manufacturers are having a hard time keeping up. Naturally, this has stirred a lot of interest in which bikes are the best. Recently,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.outsideonline.com/\"><em>Outside</em>&nbsp;magazine</a>&nbsp;conducted their annual bike test and release the results by naming their favorite&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.outsideonline.com/2412388/best-road-bikes-2020\">road bikes</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.outsideonline.com/2413404/best-mountain-bikes-2020\">mountain bikes</a>&nbsp;for 2020. Not to be outdone, our friends at&nbsp;<em><a href=\"https://www.mensjournal.com/\">Men’s&nbsp;Journal</a>&nbsp;</em>also posted their picks for the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.mensjournal.com/gear/the-best-new-gravel-bikes-to-rule-the-off-road/\">best new gravel bikes</a>&nbsp;as well. Considering the fact that riding a bike is not only